1. On je već danima* neprekidno radi. (He has been working nonstop for days.)
2. Danas je već prošlo nekoliko dana* od kad je počela epidemija. (It has already been several days since the epidemic began.)
3. Vremenom se stvari menjaju i svi se toga danima* svesno ili nesvesno bojimo. (Things change over time, and we all consciously or unconsciously fear it for days.)
4. On je tih danima* bez prestanka govorio. (He was talking nonstop for days.)
5. Tek onda smo shvatili da ćemo nekoliko dana* biti zarobljeni u hotelu. (Only then we realized that we would be trapped in the hotel for days.)